title: Sepolia: Could not process block
body:
Trying to run sync with geth and see in logs these messages:
`could not process block: could not validate new payload: method not found: received an undefined execution engine error`

prysm: v3.2.2
network: sepolia
geth: v1.11.2
then sometimes it is passed, but in case if prysm or node was rebooted there is no way to make it works, it is stuck on some block and sync is not going on
That is very odd, since we run this combination in our infra and it is fine. Can you verify the versions you are running again ? Do you have any sort of middleware between the beacon-node/geth ?

Yes, Im sure about versions.
here is how I start services:
`/usr/bin/geth --sepolia --syncmode "light" --http --http.api net,eth,personal,web3,engine,admin,debug --authrpc.vhosts=localhost --authrpc.jwtsecret=/data_eth/ethereum/consensus/prysm/jwt.hex --datadir /data_eth/database`

`/data_eth/ethereum/consensus/prysm/prysm.sh beacon-chain --execution-endpoint=http://localhost:8551 --sepolia --jwt-secret=/data_eth/ethereum/consensus/prysm/jwt.hex --datadir=/data_eth/database --verbosity debug --checkpoint-sync-url=https://sepolia.checkpoint-sync.ethdevops.io --genesis-beacon-api-url=https://sepolia.checkpoint-sync.ethdevops.io`
